# Full workflow config: all parameters with consistent naming
# Usage: source workflow_config_full.env && ./run_retrieval_rerank_pipeline.sh
#
# Naming: TOP_K = retrieval depth (same concept in BM25/Dense/Hybrid/Reranker).
# Scripts use different flags internally (k_eval, topk, cap, candidate_limit) but
# all are set from TOP_K unless overridden by stage-specific vars below.

# ---------- Ground truth (eval metrics) ----------
# HAVE_GROUND_TRUTH=1   # set to 0 to skip all eval metrics (BM25, Dense, Hybrid, Rerank)

# ---------- Shared (paths + retrieval depth) ----------
# Optional: override SCRIPT_DIR used by run_retrieval_rerank_pipeline.sh.
# By default, SCRIPT_DIR is the directory containing run_retrieval_rerank_pipeline.sh.
# Set SHARED_SCRIPTS_DIR when these scripts are vendored into another project or copied elsewhere.
# SHARED_SCRIPTS_DIR=/absolute/path/to/shared_scripts

WORKFLOW_OUTPUT_DIR=/path/to/output/full_run
# Query streams: at least one of INPUT_JSONL (primary) or INPUT_BATCH_JSONLS (space-separated) must be set.
# Every path must end with .jsonl. Convert official BioASQ task JSON with:
#   python3 scripts/public/format/bioasq_json_to_queries_jsonl.py --input task.json --output queries.jsonl
INPUT_JSONL=/path/to/training.jsonl
INPUT_BATCH_JSONLS="/path/to/test1.jsonl  /path/to/test2.jsonl"

# DOCS_JSONL: used by reranker (candidate docs) and by evidence steps (title/abstract lookup).
DOCS_JSONL=/path/to/literature.jsonl

# Retrieval depth: max docs per query (used by BM25 k_eval, Dense topk, Hybrid bm25_topk/cap/k_max_eval, Reranker candidate_limit)
TOP_K=5000
# Comma-separated K values for recall metrics (MeanR@K, etc.)
RECALL_KS=50,100,200,300,400,500,1000,2000,5000

# ---------- Index paths ----------
BM25_INDEX_PATH=/path/to/terrier_index_full
DENSE_INDEX_DIR=/path/to/dense_index_full

# ---------- Query text fields (optional) ----------
# Single field: passed to that stage as --query-field (e.g. body, body_hyde, body_expansion_long).
# Comma-separated (no spaces or trim spaces): run one retrieval/rerank per field under _sub_<field>/,
# then weighted RRF-fuse into the canonical bm25/runs, dense/runs, rerank/runs (same downstream paths).
# Fusion defaults: equal weights 1/N; k_rrf=60 (override per stage below).
# BM25_QUERY_FIELD=body
# DENSE_QUERY_FIELD=body,body_hyde
# RERANK_QUERY_FIELD=body
# BM25_QUERY_FUSION_WEIGHTS=0.5,0.5       # optional; order matches field order in BM25_QUERY_FIELD
# BM25_QUERY_FUSION_K_RRF=60
# DENSE_QUERY_FUSION_WEIGHTS=0.5,0.5
# DENSE_QUERY_FUSION_K_RRF=60
# RERANK_QUERY_FUSION_WEIGHTS=0.5,0.5
# RERANK_QUERY_FUSION_K_RRF=60
# (Snippet step 6 uses the same RERANK_QUERY_FIELD / RERANK_QUERY_FUSION_* when comma-separated.)
# Per-query adaptive body weight (default: equal 1/N). Body (first field) gets this weight;
# remaining (1 - body_weight) is split equally among active non-body fields per query.
# Useful with variable facets. Only used when *_QUERY_FUSION_WEIGHTS is not set for that stage.
# BM25_QUERY_BODY_WEIGHT=0.5
# DENSE_QUERY_BODY_WEIGHT=0.5
# RERANK_QUERY_BODY_WEIGHT=0.5

# ---------- BM25 + RM3 ----------
# BM25_INDEX_PATH (required) see above
# Optional overrides (leave unset to use defaults or TOP_K):
# BM25_JAVA_MEM=8g
# BM25_THREADS=4
# BM25_TOP_K=5000          # override retrieval depth for BM25 only (default: TOP_K)
# BM25_RM3_FEEDBACK_POOL=50 # k_feedback: docs used for RM3 expansion
# BM25_RM3_FB_DOCS=20       # RM3 fb_docs
# BM25_RM3_FB_TERMS=30      # RM25 fb_terms
# BM25_RM3_LAMBDA=0.6       # RM3 lambda
# BM25_INCLUDE_BASELINE=1   # set to 1 to also evaluate plain BM25 (--include_bm25)
# BM25_DISABLE_RM3=1        # set to 1 to disable RM3 entirely and run plain BM25 only
# BM25_NO_EVAL=1            # set to 1 to skip metrics, only write runs
# BM25_SAVE_RUNS=1          # set to 1 to save run TSVs (default in pipeline)
# BM25_SAVE_PER_QUERY=1     # set to 1 for per-query CSV
# BM25_SAVE_ZERO_RECALL=1   # set to 1 for zero-recall report
# BM25_NO_EXCLUDE_TEST_QIDS=1  # set to 1 to keep test qids in train set

# ---------- Dense ----------
# DENSE_INDEX_DIR (required) see above
# DENSE_TOP_K=5000          # override retrieval depth for Dense (default: TOP_K)
# DENSE_EF_SEARCH=          # HNSW ef_search override (default from index meta.json)
# DENSE_EF_CAP=2000         # cap on ef_search for speed
# DENSE_BATCH_SIZE=256
# DENSE_DEVICE=cpu         # cpu, cuda, mps
# DENSE_MODEL_NAME=        # override SentenceTransformer model from index meta
# DENSE_NO_EVAL=1          # set to 1 to skip metrics, only write runs
# DENSE_SAVE_PER_QUERY=1   # set to 1 for per-query CSV

# ---------- Hybrid ----------
# HYBRID_CAP=5000          # fusion output cap (default: TOP_K)
# HYBRID_K_MAX_EVAL=5000   # max rank for evaluation (default: TOP_K)
# HYBRID_MODE=default      # default or sweep
# HYBRID_K_RRF=150         # RRF k (default mode)
# HYBRID_W_BM25=1.0
# HYBRID_W_DENSE=1.0
# HYBRID_WEIGHTS=1.0,1.0;2.0,1.0;1.0,2.0   # sweep mode weight pairs
# HYBRID_K_RRF_LIST=60,100 # sweep mode RRF k list
# HYBRID_JOBS=4            # parallel processes
# HYBRID_NO_EVAL=1         # set to 1 to skip metrics, only write runs
# HYBRID_NO_PLOTS=1        # set to 1 to disable plots
# HYBRID_SAVE_PLOTS=1      # set to 1 to force plots

# ---------- Reranker + Evidence (global: PubMed/literature corpus) ----------
# Set to run reranker and, after RRF fusion, to produce post_rerank_*.jsonl and evidence/*_contexts.jsonl.
# RERANK_CANDIDATE_LIMIT=2000   # max candidates per query (default: TOP_K). Pipeline uses min(RERANK_CANDIDATE_LIMIT, HYBRID_CAP) then clamps to 100–2000.
# RERANK_KS_RECALL=50,100,200,300,400,500,1000,2000,5000  # default: RECALL_KS
# RERANK_MODEL=BAAI/bge-reranker-v2-m3
# RERANK_MODEL_DEVICE=auto     # auto, cuda, mps, cpu
# RERANK_MODEL_BATCH=16
# RERANK_MODEL_MAX_LENGTH=640
# RERANK_DISABLE_METRICS=1     # set to 1 when no ground truth
# RERANK_USE_MULTI_GPU=1
# RERANK_NUM_GPUS=0            # 0 = all
# RERANK_RERANKER_TYPE=llm     # cross_encoder (default) or llm (FlagLLMReranker, e.g. bge-reranker-v2-gemma)
# RERANK_USE_LLM=1             # alternative toggle: set to 1 to use LLM reranker (same as RERANK_RERANKER_TYPE=llm)
# RERANK_LLM_USE_FP16=1        # FP16 for LLM reranker (default: 1). Set to 0 to disable.
# RERANK_LLM_USE_BF16=0        # BF16 for LLM reranker (default: 0). Set to 1 to enable.

# ---------- RRF fusion (Hybrid + Rerank, top-10) ----------
# Enabled by default; pass --no-rrf-fusion to pipeline to skip,
# or set RUN_RRF_FUSION=0 below (env equivalent).
# RUN_RRF_FUSION=0            # set to 0 to skip RRF fusion (same as --no-rrf-fusion)
# Pool defaults are in the pipeline: 50 for baseline, 200 for snippet-only. Uncomment below to override.
# RRF_POOL_TOP_RERANK=50      # top-K from reranker for fusion pool (must be <= RERANK_CANDIDATE_LIMIT)
# RRF_POOL_TOP_HYBRID=50      # top-K from hybrid stage-1 for fusion pool (must be <= HYBRID_CAP)
# RRF_POOL_TOP=               # (deprecated) sets both RRF_POOL_TOP_RERANK and RRF_POOL_TOP_HYBRID
# RRF_K_RRF=60                # RRF K parameter in 1/(K+rank)
# RRF_W_BGE=0.8               # weight for BGE rerank scores
# RRF_W_HYBRID=0.2            # weight for Hybrid scores (default: 1 - RRF_W_BGE if unset)

# ---------- Post-fusion global rerank score cutoff (t*) ----------
# Optional filter applied after post_rerank_fusion / post_rerank_fusion_snippet RRF fusion: keep docs whose
# reranker score (from rerank/cross_encoder/runs) is >= RERANK_TSTAR, with a floor safeguard and optional cap.
# When enabled, writes post_rerank_fusion_tstar/ and post_rerank_fusion_snippet_tstar/; baseline evidence, snippet
# step 6, and final doc-side fusion read those dirs instead of unfused runs. Compare plots (rerank vs hybrid)
# stay under post_rerank_fusion/ and post_rerank_fusion_snippet/figures (pre-t* fusion diagnostic); t* cutoffs report under *_tstar/.
# RERANK_TSTAR_ENABLE=0       # set to 1 to enable (requires RERANK_TSTAR)
# RERANK_TSTAR=              # threshold on reranker score (required when ENABLE=1); same var for CE or LLM rerankers
# RERANK_TSTAR_FLOOR=5       # min docs kept per query (top-up from fused order if threshold removes too many)
# RERANK_TSTAR_CAP=          # optional extra cap after thresholding (unset = no cap beyond upstream pool size). Must be >= FLOOR if set.
# With comma-separated RERANK_QUERY_FIELD, t* uses max(raw reranker score) across rerank/cross_encoder/_sub_<field>/runs, not fused rerank/cross_encoder/runs RRF scores.

# ---------- Snippet RRF route (--snippet-rrf) ----------
# When --snippet-rrf is active, upstream RRF pool defaults to 200 (see run_retrieval_rerank_pipeline.sh).
# For a standalone example config dedicated to snippet-rrf, see workflow_config_snippet.env.
# Route toggles (optional; can also be controlled purely via CLI flags):
# RUN_BASELINE=1          # build baseline evidence/generation (default: 1)
# RUN_SNIPPET_RRF=0       # run snippet-rrf route (steps 6–7, evidence/evidence_snippet/, generation/generation_snippet/)
# SNIPPET_DENSE_MODEL=abhinand/MedEmbed-small-v0.1   # SentenceTransformer for Stage A
# SNIPPET_DENSE_DEVICE=auto
# SNIPPET_DENSE_BATCH=256
# SNIPPET_N_DOCS=100
# SNIPPET_WINDOW_SIZE=3
# SNIPPET_WINDOW_STRIDE=1
# SNIPPET_TOP_W=8
# SNIPPET_CE_MODEL=              # default: same as RERANK_MODEL if set, else BAAI/bge-reranker-v2-m3
# SNIPPET_CE_DEVICE=auto
# SNIPPET_CE_BATCH=84
# SNIPPET_CE_MAX_LENGTH=512
# SNIPPET_CE_USE_MULTI_GPU=   # default: same as RERANK_USE_MULTI_GPU if unset
# SNIPPET_CE_NUM_GPUS=        # default: same as RERANK_NUM_GPUS if unset
# SNIPPET_CE_RERANKER_TYPE=   # cross_encoder (default) or llm; falls back to RERANK_RERANKER_TYPE if unset
# SNIPPET_CE_USE_LLM=         # alternative toggle: set to 1; falls back to RERANK_USE_LLM if unset
# SNIPPET_CE_LLM_USE_FP16=    # FP16 for snippet LLM reranker; falls back to RERANK_LLM_USE_FP16 (default: 1)
# SNIPPET_CE_LLM_USE_BF16=    # BF16 for snippet LLM reranker; falls back to RERANK_LLM_USE_BF16 (default: 0)
# SNIPPET_RRF_W_DOCS=0.8         # post_rerank_fusion (doc side) weight in final fusion
# SNIPPET_RRF_W_SNIPPET=0.2      # snippet_rerank weight in final fusion
# SNIPPET_FINAL_POOL=            # pool size for final fusion (both sides); default: SNIPPET_N_DOCS
# SNIPPET_RRF_K=60               # k_rrf for final fusion
# SNIPPET_CONTEXT_TOP_WINDOWS=2  # 1 or 2; with 2, second window kept only if disjoint from first

# ---------- Listwise Reranking (RankZephyr, separate container) ----------
# Runs after the main pipeline in a dedicated vLLM container (Dockerfile.listwise).
# Requires snippet/snippet_doc_fusion output (RUN_SNIPPET_RRF=1 or --snippet-rrf in the main pipeline).
# RUN_LISTWISE=0                              # set to 1 to include listwise stage in orchestration
# LISTWISE_CONTAINER_IMG=                     # container image path for listwise (Dockerfile.listwise)
# LISTWISE_SINGLE_K=15                        # docs for single-window reranking
# LISTWISE_RUN_SLIDING=0                      # set to 1 to also run sliding-window
# LISTWISE_POOL=50                            # pool size for sliding-window reranking
# LISTWISE_WINDOW=15                          # window size for sliding-window
# LISTWISE_STRIDE=5                           # stride for sliding-window
# LISTWISE_MODEL=castorini/rank_zephyr_7b_v1_full
# LISTWISE_CONTEXT_SIZE=4096                  # model context window (tokens)
# LISTWISE_MAX_SNIPPET_TOKENS=250             # per-snippet truncation limit
# LISTWISE_OUTPUT_DIR=                        # default: $WORKFLOW_OUTPUT_DIR/listwise_rerank
# LISTWISE_DISABLE_METRICS=0                  # set to 1 when no ground truth
# LISTWISE_QUERY_FIELD=body                   # question JSON key for listwise query text (e.g. body_hyde)
# RUN_GENERATION_LISTWISE=1                   # run evidence + generation on listwise output
# LISTWISE_FUSION_W_SNIPPET=0.4               # snippet_doc_fusion weight in RRF fusion
# LISTWISE_FUSION_W_LISTWISE=0.6              # listwise weight in RRF fusion
# LISTWISE_FUSION_K_RRF=20                    # k parameter in 1/(k+rank)
# LISTWISE_FUSION_POOL_TOP=15                 # pool size (both sides); sliding uses LISTWISE_POOL
# LISTWISE_FUSE_SLIDING=0                     # set to 1 to also fuse sliding-window

# ---------- Evidence (post-rerank JSON + contexts JSONL) ----------
# Runs after RRF fusion when DOCS_JSONL is set. Query JSONL is resolved per run from INPUT_JSONL and
# INPUT_BATCH_JSONLS: split name from run filename (e.g. 13B1_golden) is matched to basename without .jsonl.
# EVIDENCE_TOP_K=10              # shared default: max reranked docs per question in post_rerank_*.jsonl (default: 10).
#                                 Per-route overrides (used by run_retrieval_rerank_pipeline.sh when both routes run):
# EVIDENCE_TOP_K_BASELINE=10     # baseline route (evidence/evidence_baseline); falls back to EVIDENCE_TOP_K then 10
# EVIDENCE_TOP_K_SNIPPET=10      # snippet route (evidence/evidence_snippet); falls back to EVIDENCE_TOP_K then 10
# If t* / floor leaves fewer rows in the run TSV, fewer documents are attached — no error.

# ---------- Generation (LLM answers from contexts JSONL) ----------
# Runs after evidence when evidence/*_contexts.jsonl exist. Writes generation/*_answers.jsonl.
# GENERATION_BACKEND=ollama              # default: script's Ollama HTTP + LLAMA_API_KEY (see generate_answers.py)
# GENERATION_BACKEND=openai_compat       # OpenAI-compatible POST .../chat/completions (aliases: openrouter, openai)
#   With openai_compat: set GEN_API_BASE here (run config, non-secret). Model id: GENERATION_MODEL / --model.
#   Do NOT put API keys in this committed template. For openai_compat, GEN_API_KEY may live in gitignored
#   repo-root .env (generate_answers loads only that key from .env if unset). LLAMA_API_KEY (ollama) must
#   be exported or injected — it is not read from .env by generate_answers. GENERATION_BACKEND,
#   GENERATION_MODEL, and GEN_API_BASE must come from this sourced config or exports, not from .env.
# Route toggles: set to 0 to skip LLM generation (and rescue) for that route; evidence still built.
# RUN_GENERATION_BASELINE=1   # run generation for baseline route (default: 1)
# RUN_GENERATION_SNIPPET=1    # run generation for snippet route (default: 1)
# OpenAI-compatible example (uncomment in your private run config, not with real secrets):
# GENERATION_BACKEND=openai_compat
# GEN_API_BASE=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1
# GENERATION_MODEL=google/gemini-2.5-flash-lite:floor   # provider model id when GENERATION_BACKEND=openai_compat
# GENERATION_MODEL=llama3.3:latest       # Ollama tag when GENERATION_BACKEND=ollama (default in script)
# GENERATION_CONCURRENCY=1           # max parallel LLM calls (default: 1)
# GENERATION_MAX_CONTEXTS=8          # cap on contexts in evidence block (default: 8)
# GENERATION_MAX_CHARS_PER_CONTEXT=1300   # truncation length per context (default: 1300)
# GENERATION_SLEEP=0.5               # seconds to sleep after each LLM call (default: 0.5)
# GENERATION_SYSTEM_PATH=/path/to/custom/system.txt   # optional: override default system prompt file
# GENERATION_SCHEMAS_DIR=/path/to/custom/schemas      # optional: override default schemas directory
# After generation, rescue runs once per split (in-place). Optional override for rescue:
# GENERATION_RESCUE_TIMEOUT=300     # client timeout for rescue (default in script: 300)
# GENERATION_RESCUE_RETRY_SLEEP=120 # seconds between retries in rescue (default: 120)

